The course aims at giving students solid foundations on matrix techniques, with an emphasis on engineering. By completing this course, students are expected to
- understand important matrix operations, and their practical applications;
- understand analysis aspects in matrix factorizations and their implications in engineering;
- understand computational aspects of various matrix solutions and learn efficient tools for computing such solutions in real world; and
- understand the interplay between matrix techniques and engineering applications.
